fixed.key_facts:
Fundamental Theorem of Calculus: ∫a^b f(x) dx = F(b) - F(a), where F(x) is the antiderivative of f(x);
Indefinite Integral: ∫ 1/x² dx = -1/x;
Constant multiplication property of integrals: ∫ k f(x) dx = k ∫ f(x) dx;
Properties of definite integrals: ∫[a to b] f(x) dx = -∫[b to a] f(x) dx.
